entropy.view

Class EmptyView

  • java.lang.Object
    • entropy.view.EmptyView
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    View, ViewAsModule
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultResourcesView

    public abstract class EmptyView
extends Object
implements View, ViewAsModule
    A view that does nothing. classes inheriting from view should implement it to get a minimal set of usefull creation tools.
    • all variables created by a view should be added using onNewVar(Var)
    • all new constraints should be added to the model using post(SConstraint) instead of problem.post()
    • any call to clear() should call super.clear() and all problem-relative variables should be cleaned in the clear()
    • any call to associate(ReconfigurationProblem) should call super.associate()
    Author:
    guillaume
